{
  "page": "Pyramid",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Juan_Carlos_Barquet_slavers_bay.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/39/Juan_Carlos_Barquet_slavers_bay.jpg/350px-Juan_Carlos_Barquet_slavers_bay.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"233\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/39/Juan_Carlos_Barquet_slavers_bay.jpg/525px-Juan_Carlos_Barquet_slavers_bay.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/39/Juan_Carlos_Barquet_slavers_bay.jpg/700px-Juan_Carlos_Barquet_slavers_bay.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Juan_Carlos_Barquet_slavers_bay.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Yunkai\" title=\"Yunkai\">Yunkai</a> along <a href=\"/index.php/Slaver%27s_Bay\" title=\"Slaver&#39;s Bay\">Slaver's Bay</a>, by Juan Carlos Barquet © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Pyramids</b> are triangular buildings similar to the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pyramid\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Pyramid\">real-life structure</a>. Brick pyramids are common in the <a href=\"/index.php/Slaver_Cities\" title=\"Slaver Cities\">Slaver Cities</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Slaver%27s_Bay\" title=\"Slaver&#39;s Bay\">Slaver's Bay</a>, and are used as palaces and fortifications by the slave-owning nobility of the cities.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Culture\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Culture</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Culture\">Culture</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Pyramid&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Culture\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Martina_PilcerovadaMeereenPyramids.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/89/Martina_PilcerovadaMeereenPyramids.jpg/350px-Martina_PilcerovadaMeereenPyramids.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"263\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/89/Martina_PilcerovadaMeereenPyramids.jpg/525px-Martina_PilcerovadaMeereenPyramids.jpg 1.5x, /images/8/89/Martina_PilcerovadaMeereenPyramids.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Martina_PilcerovadaMeereenPyramids.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">Meereen</a>, by Martina Pilcerova © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Good_Masters\" title=\"Good Masters\">Good Masters</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Astapor\" title=\"Astapor\">Astapor</a> light <a href=\"/index.php/Silk\" title=\"Silk\">silk</a> lanterns on the terraces of their pyramids at night.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Coin\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Coin\">coins</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Yunkai\" title=\"Yunkai\">Yunkai</a> are stamped with a stepped pyramid on one side and the <a href=\"/index.php/Harpy\" title=\"Harpy\">harpy</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Old_Empire_of_Ghis\" title=\"Old Empire of Ghis\">Ghis</a> on the other.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Tree, vines, and flowers can be grown on the terraces of pyramids,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> including figs, dates, and olives on the terraces of <a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">Meereen</a>'s buildings.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Pyramid&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Pyramid_of_Ghis\" title=\"Great Pyramid of Ghis\">Great Pyramid of Ghis</a> was destroyed by the <a href=\"/index.php/Valyrian_Freehold\" title=\"Valyrian Freehold\">Valyrian Freehold</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Ghiscari_wars\" title=\"Ghiscari wars\">Ghiscari wars</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The stepped pyramids of <a href=\"/index.php/Ghozai\" title=\"Ghozai\">Ghozai</a> were drowned by the <a href=\"/index.php/Doom_of_Valyria\" title=\"Doom of Valyria\">Doom of Valyria</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Pyramid&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Pyramid&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a> sees stepped pyramids among the buildings of <a href=\"/index.php/Vaes_Dothrak\" title=\"Vaes Dothrak\">Vaes Dothrak</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Pyramid&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Daenerys takes the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Pyramid\" title=\"Great Pyramid\">Great Pyramid</a> as her abode after the successful <a href=\"/index.php/Siege_of_Meereen\" title=\"Siege of Meereen\">siege of Meereen</a>. The master of the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Indigo_Star\" title=\"Indigo Star\">Indigo Star</a></i> informs her that each pyramid in <a href=\"/index.php/Astapor\" title=\"Astapor\">Astapor</a> hosts an armed camp in the aftermath of <a href=\"/index.php/Fall_of_Astapor\" title=\"Fall of Astapor\">that city's fall</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Pyramid&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Sons_of_the_Harpy\" title=\"Sons of the Harpy\">Sons of the Harpy</a> plot against Daenerys from within <a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">Meereen</a>'s pyramids in response to her abolition of <a href=\"/index.php/Slavery\" title=\"Slavery\">slavery</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Daenerys, now <a href=\"/index.php/Queen_of_Meereen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Queen of Meereen\">Queen of Meereen</a>, imposes a tax of a hundred pieces of <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">gold</a> from every pyramid for every <a href=\"/index.php/Freedman\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Freedman\">freedman</a> killed in the city, and she demands that each pyramid send her a boy and a girl to serve as <a href=\"/index.php/Cupbearers_of_Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Cupbearers of Daenerys Targaryen\">her cupbearers</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Many pyramids in Astapor are despoiled amid the city's <a href=\"/index.php/Siege_of_Astapor\" title=\"Siege of Astapor\">capture by Yunkai'i</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Pyramid&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Martina_Pilcerovad_Astapor.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1c/Martina_Pilcerovad_Astapor.jpg/350px-Martina_Pilcerovad_Astapor.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"263\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1c/Martina_Pilcerovad_Astapor.jpg/525px-Martina_Pilcerovad_Astapor.jpg 1.5x, /images/1/1c/Martina_Pilcerovad_Astapor.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Martina_Pilcerovad_Astapor.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Astapor\" title=\"Astapor\">Astapor</a>, by Martina Pilcerova © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Even through the thickness of her sandals, she could feel the warmth of the red bricks underfoot. Waves of heat rose off them shimmering to make the stepped pyramids of <a href=\"/index.php/Astapor\" title=\"Astapor\">Astapor</a> around the plaza seem half a dream.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Closer to <a href=\"/index.php/Slaver%27s_Bay\" title=\"Slaver&#39;s Bay\">the bay</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Astapor\" title=\"Astapor\">the city</a> presented a fairer face. The great brick pyramids lined the shore, the largest four hundred feet high. All manner of trees and vines and flowers grew on their broad terraces, and the winds that swirled around them smelled green and fragrant.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Dany broke her fast under the persimmon tree that grew in the terrace garden, watching her <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragons</a> chase each other about the apex of the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Pyramid\" title=\"Great Pyramid\">Great Pyramid</a> where the huge bronze <a href=\"/index.php/Harpies\" title=\"Harpies\">harpy</a> once stood. <a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">Meereen</a> had a score of lesser pyramids, but none stood even half as tall.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>You have no lack of enemies, Your Grace. You can see their pyramids from <a href=\"/index.php/Queen%27s_apartments_(Great_Pyramid)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Queen&#39;s apartments (Great Pyramid)\">your terrace</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Pyramid_of_Zhak\" title=\"Pyramid of Zhak\">Zhak</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Pyramid_of_Hazkar\" title=\"Pyramid of Hazkar\">Hazkar</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Pyramid_of_Ghazeen\" title=\"Pyramid of Ghazeen\">Ghazeen</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Pyramid_of_Merreq\" title=\"Pyramid of Merreq\">Merreq</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Pyramid_of_Loraq\" title=\"Pyramid of Loraq\">Loraq</a>, all the old slaving families. <a href=\"/index.php/Pyramid_of_Pahl\" title=\"Pyramid of Pahl\">Pahl</a>. Pahl, most of all.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Skahaz_mo_Kandaq\" title=\"Skahaz mo Kandaq\">Skahaz mo Kandaq</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>He could close his eyes and see them still: flames whirling from brick pyramids larger than any castle he had ever seen, <a href=\"/index.php/Siege_of_Astapor\" title=\"Siege of Astapor\">plumes of greasy smoke</a> coiling upward like great black snakes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Quentyn_Martell\" title=\"Quentyn Martell\">Quentyn Martell</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Pyramid&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n